Edged Energy Atlanta Data Center proposes the construction of a data center in Atlanta, Fulton County, Georgia (Atlanta ozone attainment area). It will consist of 75 diesel engines sets, called PowerBlocks: 18 four-engine and 57 six-engine PowerBlocks. Each PowerBlock consists of either four or six 932 bhp Volvo diesel engines, Model TWD1673GE, driving a generator with a total electrical output of 2,500 and 3,750 kWe, respectively, totaling to 414 engines. All engines will be U.S. EPA certified Tier 4 diesel engines, model year 2023 or later. Each four-engine PowerBlock will have one (1) 4,400-gallon diesel storage tank and each six-engine PowerBlock will have one (1) 6,600-gallon diesel storage tank. Each engine will be equipped with a Selective Catalytic Reduction (SCR) device with urea storage. The PowerBlocks are expected to be installed, starting in January 2024. (pg 1) PDF-ON-28932.pdf
